data.description: Beautiful, well maintained home on large, wooded, lake front lot. Mountainesque views from most rooms. Gorgeous updated kitchen with stained cabinets, solid surface counter tops, a nice-sized island with integrated stainless steel cook top, and all kitchen appliances - stove, refrigerator, dishwasher, built-in microwave and wall oven. Roof, all windows, and HVAC have been replaced relatively recently.  The great room offers a lovely stacked stone fireplace, a built-in wet bar, easy access to the over sized rear deck, and expansive lake views. Special, informal second front entry doubles as a nice mudroom and is located close to the washer dryer area. Same family has owned the home for 43 years (since 1975) and has taken very good care of it as will be apparent when you walk through. Just needs a little paint and new carpet to make it your own for the next 43 years. Seller will help start that legacy by offering a generous carpet allowance.   Be sure to bring your avian enthusiast clients to see this one. There is a veritable wildlife sanctuary on and around the lake.
